cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.DS

The paper focuses on optimizing hyperparameters of deep neural networks, which is a common problem in machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the experiments are conducted on image benchmark datasets, indicating a potential fit for cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also discusses the sensitivity of deep neural networks, which is a topic in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The proposed method involves reverse-mode automatic differentiation, which is a technique used in cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper discusses memory consumption, which is a topic in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
